Package: seurust
Title: Rust Native Kernels for Seurat
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Nebil", family = "Ibrahim",
           email = "nebilibrahim@microsoft.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person(given = "Rahul", family = "Satija",
           role = "ctb",
           comment = "Original Seurat native APIs"),
    person("Satija Lab and Collaborators",
           role = "cph",
           comment = "Original Seurat / ModularityOptimizer code")
    )
Description: Provides Rust/extendr reimplementations of performance-critical
    Seurat native routines such as log-normalization, sparse row scaling,
    shared nearest-neighbor graph construction, and integration helpers.
    Install alongside Seurat to use the same function signatures with a
    Rust backend. Builds require a Rust toolchain; CRAN source builds use
    vendored crates for offline compilation.
